.PP
Most familiar units, abbreviations, and metric prefixes are
recognized by the \*Lunits\*O command, together with the following:
.VL 4m
.LI "\*Lpi\*O"
Ratio of circumference to diameter.
.LI "\*Lc\*O"
Speed of light.
.LI "\*Le\*O"
Charge on an electron.
.LI "\*Lg\*O"
Acceleration of gravity.
.LI "\*Lforce\*O"
Same as \*Lg\*O.
.LI "\*Lmole\*O"
Avogadro's number.
.LI "\*Lwater\*O"
Pressure head per unit height of water.
.LI "\*Lau\*O"
Astronomical unit.
.LE
.PP
The \*L-\*O argument causes \*Lunits\*O to display a list of all
known units and their conversion values.  The \*Vfile\*O argument
specifies an alternative \*Lunits\*O file to be used instead of
